title: Grateful Dead Live at Greek Theatre, U. Of California on 1989-08-19
lineage: Tascam DA-20 (DAT)-> Tascam CDRW4U -> EAC (secure) -> CDWave (tracking) -> CDR -> SHN (MKWact), from Oade DATs, by Matt Shapiro; EAC'd and SHN'd by jim

reviews.review_text:
outstanding! this recording smokes!
yet another fine work from the Oades.

the performance is "like a swiss watch" as well.
great china>rider.
Words will never describe Just listen to "The Other One" and you'll have an idea of what this show was like.  There aren't enough stars for rating this show.

E=MC2 Some consider 89 pretty formularic...Perhaps, but the formula worked!! This tape is such a fun ride - 

great Brent...
Bobby's pretty much on...
Jerry's having fun at the Greek...so were we. 

Energy is tremendous granted, for 89, but it was a great August out west. 

This is a very strong audience tape, quality-wise --- donot skip this one.

magical ethereal uncle john's band Garcia's solos on this song [the Dead's masterpiece], which consist of delicate countermelodies, are most beautiful and poignant -- they are among his best work, and the overall work of the band on this is also outstanding

Great sound Just wanted to reiterate how great of an AUD recording this is. I'm pretty much a soundboard snob, but those Oade boys sure did a number on this one. In addition to that, you have a greatest hits - style setlist in the second set, albeit very predictable. Fun tape, excellent sound.

Superb Audience recording Oade Bros did a great job on this recording, nice stereo and dynamic range, sounds like you are there! The levels could have been a little higher, but otherwise a really good recording. the levels can be fixed easily, IMHO. Powerhouse set and a KILLER performance from the boys...summer '89 is one the Dead's best tours in their career.

Recommended to me by Paul Hunt F.L. USA  My deadhead friend come over the pond to the UK this week 9/19/2016 we always get together and discuss Dead shows and he recommended this show. Well what can I say he was right this show is outstanding a must for any serious DeadHead
